<problem display_name="Solve for A" linenum="83" tex_filename="./block2/morematrixops.tex" showanswer="finished" attempts="1" rerandomize="per_student">
  <text>
    <p>
Suppose that [mathjaxinline]A,B,C,D[/mathjaxinline] are all invertible [mathjaxinline]n\times n[/mathjaxinline] matrices such that [mathjaxinline]DA^{-1}B^{-1}= C^{-1}[/mathjaxinline]. Solve for [mathjaxinline]A[/mathjaxinline]. </p>
    <p>
      <multiplechoiceresponse>
        <choicegroup direction="vertical">
          <choice correct="false" name="1">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=DCB^{-1}[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="2">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=DB^{-1}C[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="true" name="3">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=B^{-1}CD[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="4">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=BCD^{-1}[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="5">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=D^{-1}CB[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="6">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=CB^{-1}D[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="7">
            <text> None of the above</text>
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>
    </p>
    <p>
      <solution>
        <font color="blue">Answer: </font>
        <font color="blue">
          <p>
 If we multiply on both sides of the equation by [mathjaxinline]D^{-1}[/mathjaxinline] from the left, we obtain </p>
          <table id="a0000000121" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]A^{-1}B^{-1}= D^{-1}C^{-1}.[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
          <p>
 Multiplying by [mathjaxinline]B[/mathjaxinline] on the right yields </p>
          <table id="a0000000122" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]A^{-1}= D^{-1}C^{-1}B.[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
          <p>
 Finally, we invert both sides: </p>
          <table id="a0000000123" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]A = (D^{-1}C^{-1}B)^{-1}= B^{-1}CD.[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </font>
      </solution>
    </p>
  </text>
</problem>
